doc.after: After the original model, Boeing developed an increased gross weight variant of the 777-200 with greater range and payload capability.[70] Initially named 777-200IGW,[71] the 777-200ER first flew on October 7, 1996,[72] received FAA and JAA certification on January 17, 1997,[73] and entered service with British Airways on February 9, 1997.[73] Offering greater long-haul performance, the variant became the most widely ordered version of the aircraft through the early 2000s.[70] On April 2, 1997, a Malaysia Airlines -200ER named "Super Ranger" broke the great circle "distance without landing" record for an airliner by flying eastward from Boeing Field, Seattle to Kuala Lumpur, a distance of 10,823 nautical miles (20,044Â km), in 21 hours and 23 minutes.[65]
